@startuml Render Loop Architecture with Throbber
!theme plain
title "NaturalLanguageOrchestrator::handle_query - Render Loop with Throbber"

== Code Structure ==

box "Main Task (handle_query)"
  participant "Orchestrator" as orchestrator
  participant "UI Render" as ui_render
  participant "Throbber State" as throbber_state
end box

box "Async Runtime (tokio)"
  participant "tokio::select!" as select_loop
  participant "LLM Future" as llm_future
  participant "Sleep Timer" as sleep_timer
  participant "Cancel Token" as cancel_token
end box

== Initialization ==
orchestrator -> throbber_state: state.mode = WaitingLLM
orchestrator -> throbber_state: state.start_throbber()
orchestrator -> ui_render: render(state) [initial]
note right of ui_render
  First render shows:
  |~| $ (static before animation starts)

  Note: Animation thread takes ~10ms
  to become observable
end note

orchestrator -> select_loop: Create llm_future with cancel_token
note right of select_loop
  Pin the LLM query future
  Set up for repeated polling
  in select! loop
end note

== Main Select Loop ==
loop until LLM completes or cancelled
  select_loop -> select_loop: "biased" branch priority
  note right of select_loop
    biased;
    1. result (LLM) - highest priority
    2. cancel_token - moderate priority
    3. sleep - lowest priority

    Prioritize completion over rendering
  end note

  par Polled in Order
    select_loop -> llm_future: Poll LLM query future
    note right of llm_future
      Returns Poll::Pending if still waiting
      Returns Poll::Ready(Ok/Err) on completion
    end note
  or Check Cancellation
    select_loop -> cancel_token: cancelled()
    note right of cancel_token
      Checks if SIGINT (Ctrl+C) pressed
      User initiated cancellation
    end note
  or Wait for Render Interval
    select_loop -> sleep_timer: sleep(100ms)
    note right of sleep_timer
      Minimum 100ms between renders
      Matches throbber animation rate
    end note
  end

  == Render Path (triggered by sleep) ==
  opt sleep timer fires && LLM still pending
    select_loop -> ui_render: render(state)
    note right of ui_render
      Main thread reads:
      - throbber.is_running() = true
      - throbber.symbol() = current frame
      - Renders prompt with animated symbol

      Result shown in terminal:
      |⠋| $ → |⠙| $ → |⠹| $ ...
    end note
  end

  == Completion Path ==
  opt LLM completes first (poll returns Ready)
    select_loop -> orchestrator: "result" branch
    orchestrator -> orchestrator: match llm_result { ... }
    orchestrator -> throbber_state: state.stop_throbber()
    note right of throbber_state
      Sets active flag to false
      Animation thread exits
    end note
    orchestrator -> orchestrator: handle_query_result(result, state)
    select_loop -> select_loop: break loop
  end

  == Cancellation Path ==
  opt cancel_token fires (user pressed Ctrl+C)
    select_loop -> orchestrator: "cancelled" branch
    orchestrator -> throbber_state: state.stop_throbber()
    orchestrator -> throbber_state: state.mode = Normal
    select_loop -> select_loop: break loop
  end
end

== Final Render ==
orchestrator -> ui_render: render(state)
note right of ui_render
  Final render after loop exit:
  - Throbber stopped
  - Prompt back to "|~|"
  - Response/approval/question displayed
  - Terminal ready for next input
end note

== Timing Constants ==
note over select_loop, sleep_timer
  ANIMATION_INTERVAL_MS = 100
  RENDER_INTERVAL_MS = 100

  Both synchronized to 10 FPS:
  - Throbber updates every 100ms
  - Render happens every 100ms
  - Animation appears smooth and responsive
  - 10 FPS is fast enough for fluid animation
    while not consuming too much CPU
end note

== Design Rationale ==
note over orchestrator, cancel_token
  Why tokio::select! with render loop?

  Alternative: Just wait for LLM response
  - Problem: No visual feedback
  - User sees frozen terminal
  - No indication of progress

  This approach:
  + User sees animated throbber
  + Can cancel with Ctrl+C
  + Responsive to user actions
  + Clean async/await syntax
  + Priority branch avoids render thrashing
end note

@enduml
